rmediate `Vec` unnecessarily\n\n**File:** `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs`, lines ~648-658\n\n**Current:**\n```rust\nlet fetchable: Vec<_> = targets\n    .iter()\n    .filter(|t| t.config().capabilities.fetch)\n    .cloned()\n    .collect();\n\nif fetchable.is_empty() {\n    return Err(...);\n}\n```\n\n**Suggestion:** This is acceptable since the vector is small (handful of targets), but if you wanted to avoid the allocation, you could filter during the futures construction and check emptiness differently. However, given that `fetchable` is also indexed later in the results loop (`fetchable[i]`), the collected Vec is actually the cleanest approach here. **No change needed** -- the current approach is the right tradeoff for readability.\n\n---\n\n### Finding 7: Doc comments reference bitflag-style names (`QUORUM_CREDIT`, `FETCH`, `SEND`)\n\n**Files:**\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-transport/src/target.rs`, line 486: `SEND | FETCH | QUORUM_CREDIT`\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-transport/src/coordinator.rs`, line 798: `QUORUM_CREDIT`\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs`, line 647: `FETCH`\n\n**Current:** Doc comments use `SCREAMING_CASE` names like `QUORUM_CREDIT` and pipe syntax like `SEND | FETCH | QUORUM_CREDIT`, but the actual implementation uses plain boolean struct fields (`capabilities.quorum_credit`).\n\n**Suggestion:** Use field-style names in docs to match the implementation:\n- `SEND | FETCH | QUORUM_CREDIT` becomes `send, fetch, quorum_credit` or simply \"all capabilities\"\n- `QUORUM_CREDIT capability` becomes `quorum_credit` or \"quorum credit\"\n\n**Why:** Readers looking at the docs and then the code will see a mismatch between the documentation's implied bitflag design and the actual boolean struct. Minor, but avoids the \"where is this constant defined?\" question.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| # | Finding | Effort | Impact |\n|---|---------|--------|--------|\n| 1 | Derive `Default` on `TargetCapabilities` | Low | Medium -- reduces boilerplate, future-proofs |\n| 2 | Consistent delegation style in coordinator mutations | Low | Low -- style consistency |\n| 3 | `quorum_target_count` via `quorum_target_ids` | Low | Medium -- eliminates duplicated logic |\n| 4 | Rename `targets_where` to `targets_by_capability` | Low | Low -- naming consistency |\n| 5 | Extract test helper for coordinator+pool setup | Low | Low -- reduces test noise |\n| 6 | `fetch_from_targets` intermediate Vec | N/A | No change needed |\n| 7 | Doc comment naming mismatch | Low | Low -- documentation accuracy |\n\nFindings 1 and 3 are the most worthwhile changes. Finding 4 is a judgment call -- the current name is not wrong, just slightly inconsistent with `targets_by_kind`. The rest are minor polish.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>33199</total_tokens><tool_uses>6</tool_uses><duration_ms>69397</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/36b495c0-95b9-49fc-8523-b911e74011a9/tasks/a807cee0d7bdd1e90.output",
