R | 4 | Missing `verified_peer_index`, no periodic refresh, no stale-peer lifecycle, no channel binding |\n| MINOR | 2 | Timing side-channel on candidate iteration, config field name mismatch |\n| COMPLIANT | 7 | Event subscription, rk matching, HTTP skip, target add/remove, resource limits, enabled default, challenge-response |\n| INFO | 2 | Post-download size check, identity response format |\n\nThe most impactful gaps are the missing periodic refresh and stale-peer lifecycle. Without these, the controller cannot detect DHCP reassignment or clean up peers that disappear without mDNS goodbye packets, which directly undermines the WHITEPAPER 11.6 requirement for \"stale identities removed from Direct tier automatically.\" Channel binding (SEC-3) is a known deferral (Chunk 5). The timing side-channel (SEC-2) is a straightforward fix -- accumulate the match result across all candidates without early return.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>71239</total_tokens><tool_uses>13</tool_uses><duration_ms>97265</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/36b495c0-95b9-49fc-8523-b911e74011a9/tasks/aaeb9183fb7abe5e6.output",
