ethods**.\n\n**Minor deviations:**\n\n- **m13 — `send_text()` not migrated to `send_text_tiered()`**: Delivery phase not surfaced in UI.\n- `MessageReceiver` not deprecated (reiterated).\n- `direct_peers` missing deprecation warning for entries without `public_id`.\n\n**Compliant:** Client type migration, EDGE-6 graceful degradation, EDGE-3 advertise-after-bind, background browse, controller spawn, configured peers preserved, disabled-feature isolation.\n\n#### Simplifier\n\nTop findings:\n- **S1 — Triple-Option → `DiscoveryState` struct** (Medium, eliminates impossible states)\n- **S2 — Extract discovery init to `discovery::initialize()`** (Medium, reduces `App::new` length)\n- Port parsing via `SocketAddr` (Low)\n- Priority clamping helper — DRY (Low)\n- `ConfiguredTier` → `DeliveryTier` conversion — `From` impl (Low)\n\n---\n\n### Area 5: Node + Docs (`apps/node/`, `docs/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **m15 — `sign_data` not zeroized** (`api.rs:919-925`): `generate_receipt` zeroizes `sign_data`; `get_identity` does not. Inconsistent security practice.\n- **m16 — Threat model references `MAX_PEERS`** (`threat-model.md:48`): Constant no longer exists. Should reference `LanDiscoveryConfig.max_peers`.\n- Module-level doc comment in `api.rs` is stale (omits identity/health endpoints).\n- Threat model §2 understates information leak (contact-graph edge not mentioned).\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- `DefaultBodyLimit` only on `auth_routes` — public routes have no explicit cap (fine for GET-only).\n- AGENTS.md `unwrap()` ban covers library crates only — apps use `expect()` correctly.\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**Deviations:**\n\n- **Channel binding rejected in threat model but listed as Chunk 5 work in plan** — disagreement.\n- **WHITEPAPER 11.6 stale** — response format shows `node_pubkey, routing_keys, signature` but implementation returns only `signature`.\n- Threat model missing SEC-2 and SEC-5 documentation.\n- Chunk 8 (docs) not yet implemented — expected per dependency